A protein that is a neurotrophic polypeptide factor that regulates neuronal differentiation and is essential for neuronal survival, neurite growth and plasticity. It contains a signal peptide, a propeptide, and a C-terminal Nerve growth factor family (Pfam:PF00243) domain.

A protein that contains multiple TNFR/NGFR cysteine-rich region (Pfam:PF00020) within the extracellular ligand-binding domain, a type I (single pass) transmembrane domain, and a cytoplasmic Death domain (Pfam:PF00531) required for intracellular signaling.
A protein that is a translation product of the Escherichia coli K-12 cyaA gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the Escherichia coli K-12 tap gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the Escherichia coli K-12 thrB gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that binds to a specific cell surface receptor complex known as the IFN-gamma receptor (IFNGR), a complex of two IFNGR1 and two IFNGR2 chains.
An Hsp70 family chaperone that contains an ATPase and HSP90 domains.
A nodal protein that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage.

A protein that consists of an Ephrin receptor ligand binding domain (Pfam:PF01404), two copies of the Fibronectin type III domain (Pfam:PF00041), and a copy of either type of SAM domain (Sterile alpha motif) (Pfam:PF00536 or Pfam:PF07647).

A protein that consists solely of an Interferon alpha/beta domain (Pfam:PF00143) and which binds to a specific cell surface receptor complex known as the IFN-alpha receptor (IFNAR), a heterodimer of IFNAR1 and IFNAR2 chains.
A class 2 cytokine, IL-10 type that binds to a specific cell surface receptor complex known as the IFN type III receptor, a heterodimer consisting of IFNLR1 and IL-10R2.
A protein-containing complex that is a heterodimer of an alpha subunit (CGA) common to several glycoprotein hormones and a beta subunit (TSHB) unique to thyroid stimulating hormone.

A protein that has a core domain composition consisting of a PH domain (Pfam:PF00169), Protein kinase domain (Pfam:PF00069) and a Protein kinase C terminal domain (Pfam:PF00433). Mammals have three genes encoding AKT1, AKT2 and AKT3. The second messenger phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate [PIP(3)], product of phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase, acts largely through its role as a kinase activator. Binding of the pleckstrin domain to PIP(3) results in its targeting to the plasma membrane. Full activity is gained only after phosphorylation at two sites.

label.value: antiviral innate immune response receptor RIG-I

definition.value: A protein that is a translation product of the human RIGI gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a standalone version of the Hormone_1 domain (Pfam:PF00103). In the immature form, the domain is preceded by a signal peptide.

A protein that has G protein-coupled receptor (GPCR) activity. Each GPCR consists of a single polypeptide with an extracellular N-terminus, an intracellular C-terminus and seven hydrophobic transmembrane domains (TM1-TM7) linked by three extracellular loops (ECL1-ECL3) and three intracellular loops (ICL1-ICL3). GPCRs function as part of a heterotrimeric complex to transmit an extracellular signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein via the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit.
A tandem-copy polyubiquitin that is a translation product of the human UBB gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A ubiquitin-ribosomal protein eS31 fusion protein that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage. This form is the N-terminal region consisting of the Ubiquitin (Pfam:PF00240) domain. Example: UniProtKB:P62979, 1-76.

A polyubiquitin-C that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage to produce a protein consisting of a Ubiquitin (Pfam:PF00240) domain. There are nine copies of ubiquitin in polyubiquitin C. Example: UniProtKB:P0CG48, (1-76) or (77-152) or (153-228) or (229-304) or (305-380) or (381-456) or (457-532) or (533-608) or (609-684).

A ubiquitin-ribosomal protein eL40 fusion protein that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage. This form is the N-terminal region consisting of the Ubiquitin (Pfam:PF00240) domain. Example: UniProtKB:P62987, 1-76.

A polyubiquitin-B that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage to produce a protein consisting of a Ubiquitin (Pfam:PF00240) domain. There are three copies of ubiquitin in polyubiquitin B. Example: UniProtKB:P0CG47, (1-76) or (77-152) or (153-228).
A proteolytic cleavage product that gives rise to a protein that corresponds to the stand-alone version of the Ubiquitin (Pfam:PF00240) domain. Example: UniProtKB:P0CG48, 1-76.
A protein that is encoded in the genome of some Eukaryota.
A protein that contains multiple tandem copies of the Ubiquitin (Pfam:PF00240) domain within a single amino acid chain.
A protein that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.
